<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>23383</id>
    <title>docker push should try to push a new tag, and only upload the required layers</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Docker 1.11.2</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">currently the behaviour of "docker push" is to:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">* generate a list of layers</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">* push each layer</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">* create a manifest file</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">* push the manifest file</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">However, the push API, returns an error containing a list of missing layers.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">Docker push should:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">* generate a list of layers: L</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">* create a manifest file</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">* push the manifest file</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.6">* push the intersection of the error list and L</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.7">* if there's an intersection of the error list and L, push the manifest file</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">This way when you push a tag, for an existing repo you only make 1 http request.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
